  <p class="auto-style21">Canvas Draft State</p> 
  <p class="auto-style22">Draft state is a terrific new feature from Canvas which we think you will really like!&nbsp; It is optional until June 13, 2014, the last day of spring quarter.&nbsp; You may or may not use it as you choose. However, it is not something you can toggle off and on.&nbsp; Once chosen, it permanently changes the look and feel of many Canvas features.&nbsp; Take a look at the video demos below to help you decide if you want to use it.&nbsp;&nbsp; After June 13, it will become the default view.&nbsp; </p> 
  <p class="auto-style19">&nbsp;Draft State&nbsp; is a major change in the way Canvas functions and looks.&nbsp; Draft state allows you to publish and unpublish modules, assignments, quizzes, discussions and pages.&nbsp; When you add any of the options listed, you'll see a new look.&nbsp; The ultimate goal is to make adding/editing all additions to Canvas look the same and to eliminate the More Options link found on some pages.&nbsp; Now all your options are on a single page.&nbsp; Not only did they change the look of the Pages function but they also changed the way it works.&nbsp; In the old system </p> 
